title: Louis Rossmann reviews Apple self repair program for Macbooks
description:
https://www.selfservicerepair.com/home

00:00 - A crumb
00:04 - Intro
00:26 - Older video commentary on prior Apple repair programs
01:42 - Let's look at it
01:50 - Most Macbooks are not in the program
02:32 - Serial number required
02:51 - Buying individual parts is critical. 
03:04 - Let's try buying a trackpad on eBay
03:31 - Apple sells trackpad by itself, at reasonable price!
04:34 - We are not going to complain about the toolkits, leave that to gizmodo
05:24 - Keyboard repair - only top case for sale
06:02 - The difference between a keyboard & a top case
07:06 - The issue with Apple's repair philosophy
07:26 - Why we don't buy parts from Apple
07:42 - I would be ripping people off doing repairs using this system
08:07 - but Louis, it's riveted into the case!!!!!11one
09:07 - These programs make independent repair look better
10:13 - Going over the screen - only assembly for sale 
12:19 - But Louis, they have to sell the whole thing because it's adhesed together!!!!
13:35 - Logic boards for sale, but no schematics/boardviews
14:40 - Even AASPs or people in the IRP program cannot buy schematics/boardviews
14:54 - Apple's cope excuse for not making schematics/boardviews available to independent repair centers 
15:18 - We're better rated than them...
15:51 - They made audio boards available!
16:26 - This is progress, even though the program sucks
17:32 - I still can't use this for anything
18:00 - I can't use the IRP program either...
19:04  - Conclusion
20:41- kitty
